Gilts Climb as Osborne Cuts Growth Forecast, BOE Minutes Express Caution

-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 
2011-03-23T12:45:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/u-k-government-bonds-stay-higher-after-2011-growth-forecast-cut-to-1-7-.html
U.K. government bonds stayed higher
after Chancellor of the Exchequer  George Osborne  said growth
this year will be 1.7 percent, lower than a previous forecast
for a 2.1 percent expansion.  The 10-year gilt yield was five basis points lower at 3.55
percent as of 12:44 p.m. in  London , with the two-year note yield
three basis points lower at 1.26 percent.  Osborne also said the 2011-12 deficit will be 122 billion
pounds ($198 billion).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucy Meakin in London at 
 lmeakin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Daniel Tilles at 
